<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="812" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="54.[789,1382,396,823]" lastBlockId="54.[162,1380,828,2005]" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">
The relationship with congeners is uncertain but the species seems to be closely related to either 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[1004,1110,554,587]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[1161,1284,554,587]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">H. petersi</taxonomicName>
, based on limited genetic data. Specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[790,923,633,666]" name="Myanmar" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
that were previously included in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[790,898,676,705]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
under the name austenianus are now considered to represent this species, although the specimens from Meghalaya that were included under the same name may represent either this species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[653,757,828,861]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
, or a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
